cs.DC, cs.DS, cs.AR, cs.CC, cs.PL

Reasoning: 
1. cs.DC (Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing) - This paper focuses on exploring the limits of GPUs for general purpose parallel computing, which falls under the scope of distributed and parallel computing. 
2. cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) - The paper specifically studies parallel graph algorithms for list ranking and connected components, which are data structure and algorithm problems. 
3. cs.AR (Hardware Architecture) - The paper discusses the performance of GPUs for parallel computing, which is related to hardware architecture. 
4. cs.CC (Computational Complexity) - The paper explores the limits of GPUs for solving worst-case scenarios of coalescing parallel memory accesses, which is related to computational complexity. 
5. cs.PL (Programming Languages) - The paper presents guidelines for adapting PRAM graph algorithms for parallel GPU computation, which involves programming language considerations.
